criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  naïve papilla with a body temperature ≥37 °C who was diagnosed with mild to moderate
             cholangitis associated with choledocholithiasis.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  procedural failure requiring an anatomy-modifying procedure, such as a Billroth II
             subtotal gastrectomy or R-en-Y gastrojejunostomy ;

          -  stenosis of the pyloric ring ;

          -  tumor-related obstruction;

          -  failure to locate the papilla ;

          -  active peptic ulcer bleeding ;

          -  intolerance due to inadequate sedation

          -  CBD sludge;

          -  non-naïve papilla in ERCP
